{"id":561126951,"lang":"cpp","time":"1 month, 3 weeks","timestamp":1632634411,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"32 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/561126951/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"36.8 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * struct TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode *left;\n *     TreeNode *right;\n *     TreeNode() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x) : val(x), left(nullptr), right(nullptr) {}\n *     TreeNode(int x, TreeNode *left, TreeNode *right) : val(x), left(left), right(right) {}\n * };\n */\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    vector<int> v;\n    void inorder(TreeNode* root){\n        if(root!=NULL){\n            inorder(root->left);\n            if(root!=NULL)\n                v.push_back(root->val);\n            inorder(root->right);\n        }\n    }\n    bool findTarget(TreeNode* root, int k) {\n        if(root==NULL)\n            return false;\n        inorder(root);\n        for(int i=0;i<v.size()-1;i++){\n            for(int j=i+1;j<v.size();j++){\n                if(v[i]+v[j]==k){\n                    return true;\n                }\n                //cout<<v[i]<<\" \"<<v[j]<<\"\\n\";\n            }\n        }\n\n        return false;\n        \n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst"}
